Just a little worn out.

695
00:53:59,480 --> 00:54:03,080
- Mmm.
- So, how do you know he misses me?

696
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:05,560
We communicate.

697
00:54:07,040 --> 00:54:09,200
You do?

698
00:54:09,280 --> 00:54:12,360
We still talk.
All the time.

699
00:54:14,080 --> 00:54:17,080
Has he said anything
about me lately?

700
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:21,600
He knows exactly
what's goin' on with you, Joey.

701
00:54:23,520 --> 00:54:26,480
He didn't tell you
how it was gonna turn out did he?

702
00:54:28,720 --> 00:54:32,480
Do you think Dad would be
happier if we moved him out that...

703
00:54:32,560 --> 00:54:36,400
that scummy cemetery
out there under that freeway?

704
00:54:36,480 --> 00:54:40,760
And we move him out in the country,
you know? Someplace nice.

705
00:54:40,840 --> 00:54:44,280
With some birds and some trees,
you know. A river. Somethin'.

706
00:54:44,360 --> 00:54:47,520
Joey...

707
00:54:47,600 --> 00:54:51,360
whatever you're gonna give
your father, you already...

708
00:54:51,400 --> 00:54:54,560
gave him while
he was still alive.

709
00:54:59,960 --> 00:55:02,040
Do you need anything, Ma?

710
00:55:02,080 --> 00:55:05,160
No, thanks, son.

711
00:55:06,280 --> 00:55:08,880
- I gotta go out.
- Mmm.

712
00:55:28,320 --> 00:55:30,520
- Boo! Got you!
- Jesus Christ!

713
00:55:30,560 --> 00:55:33,520
- What are you doing in there?
How'd you get in there?
- I picked the lock.

714
00:55:33,600 --> 00:55:37,440
- Why'd you go in there?
What are you lookin' for?
- I was just playing a trick.

715
00:55:37,520 --> 00:55:39,560
Get outta here.

716
00:55:41,320 --> 00:55:44,400
Don't do that sort of thing!
Stay outta my room!

717
00:55:44,480 --> 00:55:47,640
- What's the matter? What did you do?
- I didn't do anything.

718
00:55:47,680 --> 00:55:50,520
Tell her to stay
outta my room! All right?

719
00:56:24,560 --> 00:56:27,960
- Get out, you hog.
You been in there for an hour.
- I'll be out in a minute.

720
00:56:30,600 --> 00:56:34,600
Come on, Kate. Cut it out.
I'm comin' out right now.

721
00:56:38,840 --> 00:56:40,800
Hurry up.

722
00:56:53,360 --> 00:56:56,520
- You gonna forgive me?
- No.

723
00:56:56,600 --> 00:56:59,560
- You sure?
- Stop it.

724
00:56:59,640 --> 00:57:03,200
All right, all right.
Just quit bugging me.

725
00:57:31,040 --> 00:57:32,880
Geez!

726
00:57:34,880 --> 00:57:36,920
Damn it!

727
00:58:53,880 --> 00:58:57,920
- Whoa!
- My god!

728
00:59:00,800 --> 00:59:05,400
Joey! Joey, what happened?
Are you hurt?

729
00:59:08,480 --> 00:59:10,960
Joey.

730
00:59:11,040 --> 00:59:14,120
Joey, did you find
the Liberty Bell money?

731
00:59:14,200 --> 00:59:18,600
Mom, look. It's a real
hundred dollar bill.

732
00:59:18,680 --> 00:59:20,960
Did you find that money, Joey?

733
00:59:21,040 --> 00:59:23,960
What does it look like?

734
00:59:24,040 --> 00:59:26,920
- You been lying to us?
- I did not lie.

735
00:59:27,000 --> 00:59:29,600
I just didn't
tell the whole truth.

736
00:59:29,680 --> 00:59:34,160
So what are you all
lookin' at?

737
00:59:34,240 --> 00:59:36,280
Here, Billy.

738
00:59:36,360 --> 00:59:40,600
Here. That'll fix the ceiling.

739
00:59:42,760 --> 00:59:46,200
Billy, redo the entire house.

740
00:59:46,240 --> 00:59:50,080
And pay off
the mortgage.

741
00:59:50,160 --> 00:59:53,440
Here, let's buy Ma...
Ma, we'll buy you...

742
00:59:53,520 --> 00:59:55,840
a summer house
on the Jersey shore.

743
00:59:55,880 --> 00:59:58,240
With your own
private fishing boat.

744
00:59:58,280 --> 01:00:02,680
With your own
private dock.

745
01:00:02,760 --> 01:00:06,680
Katie! Katie, Katie needs, uh...
braces, right?

746
01:00:06,760 --> 01:00:09,760
And, uh, she wants,
uh, a new bike.

747
01:00:09,840 --> 01:00:11,680
And she wants
to go to college.

748
01:00:11,760 --> 01:00:14,200
I don't want to be rich
if I have to go to school!

749
01:00:14,280 --> 01:00:16,920
Eleanor wants
a new wardrobe and a new TV.

750
01:00:16,960 --> 01:00:20,320
Go to Iowa and visit relatives
you never even knew that you had.

751
01:00:20,400 --> 01:00:22,240
Whoa.
W-W-W-Wait a minute.

752
01:00:22,320 --> 01:00:25,240
We don't need no money
that don't belong to us.

753
01:00:25,280 --> 01:00:28,520
Let them talk!

754
01:00:28,600 --> 01:00:31,280
- I'll take the bike and a few hundred.
- No, you won't.

755
01:00:31,360 --> 01:00:34,360
- Get in your room right now.
- She wants the bike!

756
01:00:34,400 --> 01:00:37,000
Joey, if the old man
taught us anything...

757
01:00:37,080 --> 01:00:39,880
he taught us you don't
get somethin' for nothin', right?

758
01:00:39,960 --> 01:00:43,640
No such thing
as a free lunch.

759
01:00:43,680 --> 01:00:46,680
Then what's that
in my hand, Billy?

760
01:00:46,720 --> 01:00:49,320
Billy, the old man is dead.

761
01:00:49,400 --> 01:00:52,560
Remember what it was like
when he was alive? Remember that?

762
01:00:52,640 --> 01:00:57,840
Workin' 18 hour days, his hands all
busted up. He couldn't even make a fist.

763
01:00:57,920 --> 01:01:00,760
Three, four glycerin tablets
at a time to keep his heart pumpin'?

764
01:01:00,800 --> 01:01:02,840
- You remember that? Yeah?
- Yeah, I remember.

765
01:01:02,880 --> 01:01:06,640
And if you know what's good for you,
you just leave the old man out of this.

766
01:01:06,720 --> 01:01:09,800
What good did it do him?
What good did it do him?

767
01:01:09,880 --> 01:01:13,480
His son is drinkin'
in the same bar stool that he was.

768
01:01:13,560 --> 01:01:17,200
Joey, you're gonna
clean this mess up...

769
01:01:17,280 --> 01:01:20,280
and we're gonna go down there tomorrow
morning and give that money back.

770
01:01:20,320 --> 01:01:23,560
Give it back?
What are you, nuts?

771
01:01:23,640 --> 01:01:28,440
What do you think I got
to look forward to in my life? What?

772
01:01:28,480 --> 01:01:31,680
I measure my life
in unemployment checks, Billy.

773
01:01:31,760 --> 01:01:36,000
I'm 26 years old and I live in the same
room right down the hall from my mom!

774
01:01:36,080 --> 01:01:39,160
What do I got to look forward to?
What about my family?

775
01:01:39,240 --> 01:01:42,160
What about my future?
I got nothin'!

776
01:01:42,240 --> 01:01:44,800
I can't even get my own goddamn
brother to give me work!

777
01:01:44,880 --> 01:01:47,200
Shut up! Shut up!
I do my best for you!

778
01:01:47,280 --> 01:01:49,120
- Yeah!
- The best I can!

779
01:01:49,200 --> 01:01:51,040
- You son-of-a-bitch!
- Hey, hey! Break it up! Break it up!

780
01:01:51,120 --> 01:01:53,240
- I'm keepin' the goddamn money!
- You're givin' it back!

781
01:01:53,280 --> 01:01:56,800
- You are givin' it back! You hear me?
- Eleanor! Stop it!

782
01:01:56,880 --> 01:01:59,800
- I ain't givin' shit back!
- You son-of-a-bitch!

783
01:01:59,840 --> 01:02:02,000
Eleanor, take your husband to bed.

784
01:02:02,080 --> 01:02:04,960
- You're givin' it back!
- Shut up, Billy! Go to bed!

785
01:02:05,040 --> 01:02:08,280
You're givin' that money back!
I want you outta this house
if you keep that money.

786
01:02:08,320 --> 01:02:10,640
Stop it!

787
01:02:15,360 --> 01:02:19,720
Joey. Joey, everybody
needs money to live...

788
01:02:19,800 --> 01:02:21,640
but not
this kind of money.

789
01:02:21,720 --> 01:02:26,120
No, Ma. It's found money.
The answer to our prayers.

790
01:02:28,520 --> 01:02:32,320
Your father used to say to me,
"Be careful what you pray for.

791
01:02:32,400 --> 01:02:35,320
You might get it."

792
01:02:35,400 --> 01:02:38,600
You gotta give
this money back, Joey.

793
01:02:41,120 --> 01:02:44,440
I ain't givin' it back.

794
01:02:47,360 --> 01:02:50,200
I'll say a prayer
for you, Joe.

795
01:03:10,560 --> 01:03:13,800
And that's when I seen
these guys push the car in the river.

796
01:03:13,880 --> 01:03:15,720
How many?
Two, three, four?

797
01:03:15,800 --> 01:03:19,320
Two, three, could have been more.
But it was definitely couple of few.

798
01:03:19,400 --> 01:03:21,360
What did
they look like?

799
01:03:21,440 --> 01:03:26,440
Bent noses. Mobsters. Guys that
look like they're up to no good.

800
01:03:26,520 --> 01:03:29,840
- Then what happened?
- Then they left in a fancy Caddy.

801
01:03:35,360 --> 01:03:37,720
That's the wrong car.

802
01:03:37,760 --> 01:03:39,720
What? Oh, oh, oh!

803
01:03:39,800 --> 01:03:42,800
What do you... What do you... Excuse me!
What do you mean "wrong car"?

804
01:03:42,880 --> 01:03:45,480
That's a Dodge.
We only pay for Chevelles.

805
01:03:45,560 --> 01:03:47,760
What are you talkin' about?
Where's my cash?

806
01:03:47,840 --> 01:03:51,320
- What?
- My cash. My money. My reward.

807
01:03:51,360 --> 01:03:54,440
Take it up with Hrbek.
Liberty Bell.

808
01:03:54,520 --> 01:03:57,120
You know, I took off
from work to be here.

809
01:03:57,200 --> 01:03:59,320
That's what I get
for gettin' involved with cops?

810
01:04:26,200 --> 01:04:28,040
- Hey, frogman!
- Yo.

811
01:04:28,120 --> 01:04:29,960
Right here.

812
01:04:42,560 --> 01:04:45,600
- Monica!
- Oh, god.

813
01:04:57,200 --> 01:04:59,680
Discount from book on an I.P.O.
With great cash flow.

814
01:04:59,760 --> 01:05:02,240
Sully and Sons wants to lay off
half a million shares.

815
01:05:02,320 --> 01:05:04,440
- Monica, are you listening to me?
- L-I.P.O. Great cash flow.

816
01:05:04,480 --> 01:05:07,720
- Right. Check and see if Sully
settled on that last trade.
- Yeah.

817
01:05:07,800 --> 01:05:10,200
Joe, if you're not here on business,
I don't have time for this.

818
01:05:10,240 --> 01:05:14,880
Miss Russo, I'd like to invest
$600,000 'til later tonight.

819
01:05:14,920 --> 01:05:17,640
Now, any interest you might
make on that investment...

820
01:05:17,720 --> 01:05:19,680
is yours to keep.

821
01:05:19,760 --> 01:05:23,720
Joe, it's taken me three years
to go from receptionist to new accounts.

822
01:05:23,800 --> 01:05:25,880
Get my own desk.

823
01:05:25,920 --> 01:05:27,840
It's all clear now.
So in three more years...

824
01:05:27,920 --> 01:05:31,960
you're gonna get a new desk
that's gonna be five feet away.

825
01:05:32,000 --> 01:05:34,200
And if you really
kiss ass...

826
01:05:34,240 --> 01:05:36,880
you're gonna get
your very own key to the toilet.

827
01:05:36,960 --> 01:05:40,480
Listen, Joe, I don't kiss ass.
I busted my ass to get where I am.

828
01:05:40,560 --> 01:05:42,400
So don't be disrespectful.

829
01:05:42,480 --> 01:05:44,680
Buy two first class tickets.

830
01:05:44,760 --> 01:05:47,200
I don't care where. Anywhere.
As long as it's out of the country.

831
01:05:47,280 --> 01:05:49,760
What do you expect me to do?
Risk my life for you?

832
01:05:49,840 --> 01:05:53,720
W-Where do you get off coming in
here to my place of work?

833
01:06:05,360 --> 01:06:07,600
You're crazy.

834
01:06:07,680 --> 01:06:10,680
Meet me at Dempsey's Bar
at 11:00. Don't be late.

835
01:06:11,880 --> 01:06:14,360
What if I don't show?

836
01:06:17,280 --> 01:06:20,480
Well, you'll be
that much richer.

837
01:06:21,520 --> 01:06:23,800
I love you, baby.

838
01:06:25,640 --> 01:06:29,800
Monica, yes or no. I'm still
waitin' to hear on that.
Did Sully settle on that trade?

839
01:06:29,880 --> 01:06:33,880
- Maybe, maybe not.
- This kind of opportunity
doesn't happen every day.

840
01:06:42,320 --> 01:06:44,760
Busted windshield.

841
01:06:44,840 --> 01:06:47,000
It's anybody's guess
if it's a Chevelle.

842
01:06:47,080 --> 01:06:49,600
You want me
to bring it up?

843
01:06:49,680 --> 01:06:53,840
No, let's come back tomorrow.
Yeah, bring it up.

844
01:07:00,720 --> 01:07:02,800
- How're doin', Joe?
- Hi.

845
01:07:04,400 --> 01:07:06,640
Hi, Joe. How you doin'?

846
01:07:13,760 --> 01:07:16,920
You guys got my half mil
broken down as agreed?

847
01:07:18,360 --> 01:07:20,240
Well, to get five for six,
you gotta...

848
01:07:20,320 --> 01:07:22,880
you gotta show me
the second six first.

849
01:07:24,600 --> 01:07:26,800
You're changin'
the deal on me.

850
01:07:26,880 --> 01:07:29,720
- No, we're not.
- Joe, let him see it.

851
01:07:29,800 --> 01:07:31,840
Let him see it.

852
01:07:38,560 --> 01:07:41,080
What the fuck
is this shit?

853
01:07:43,680 --> 01:07:45,440
Joe. Joe. Joe.

854
01:07:47,920 --> 01:07:51,800
I want my money.
All I want is my money.

855
01:07:51,880 --> 01:07:54,840
Just give me my money.
It's my money.

856
01:07:54,920 --> 01:07:58,800
We're doin' you a favor. What the hell
are you doin'? Put that down.

857
01:07:58,880 --> 01:08:02,720
- It's my money.
- All right. Bring him his money.

858
01:08:02,800 --> 01:08:05,920
Dino, bring him his money.
Every penny.

859
01:08:14,120 --> 01:08:19,240
You know, the only
real question with money is...

860
01:08:19,320 --> 01:08:22,040
do you posses it
or does it posses you?

861
01:08:22,080 --> 01:08:25,760
Shut up. And I don't wanna hear about
Ben Franklin havin' sex in a tree house.

862
01:08:27,200 --> 01:08:31,480
I think that,
uh, the ink...

863
01:08:31,520 --> 01:08:34,280
from the bills...

864
01:08:34,360 --> 01:08:37,120
is seeping
into your bloodstream, Joe.

865
01:08:37,200 --> 01:08:40,920
And it's, it's...
affecting your equilibrium.

866
01:08:43,160 --> 01:08:46,400
- Got your money, Joe.
- Put it on the ground.

867
01:08:50,240 --> 01:08:53,120
Against the wall. Get against the wall.
Put your hands against the wall.

868
01:08:53,200 --> 01:08:56,280
Lie down.

869
01:08:56,360 --> 01:08:59,320
Put your legs
up in the air.

870
01:09:08,000 --> 01:09:09,880
Nickels?

871
01:09:11,400 --> 01:09:13,520
Nickels?

872
01:09:19,040 --> 01:09:22,240
Quarters?
You gave me quarters?

873
01:09:22,320 --> 01:09:24,800
Well, the deal was...

874
01:09:24,880 --> 01:09:27,960
to break down
the money, Joe.

875
01:09:28,040 --> 01:09:31,280
You did not specify
what denominations.

876
01:09:31,360 --> 01:09:34,040
You evil son-of-a-bitch.

877
01:09:34,080 --> 01:09:38,640
You give me my money or I'm gonna shoot
you. You're gamblin' with your life.

878
01:09:38,720 --> 01:09:40,960
- Joe, don't be a punk, huh?
- Legs up!

879
01:09:41,040 --> 01:09:43,160
They're up.

880
01:09:43,200 --> 01:09:46,680
You're not gonna shoot me.

881
01:09:46,760 --> 01:09:49,840
- How do you know?
- Because if you shoot me...

882
01:09:49,920 --> 01:09:54,280
you got nothing,
nothing.

883
01:09:54,360 --> 01:09:58,720
You got 600,000 bucks
squirreled away somewhere, Joe.

884
01:09:58,800 --> 01:10:00,640
Go home.

885
01:10:09,480 --> 01:10:12,320
Put the gun down, Joe.
You'll be able to carry more money.

886
01:10:33,920 --> 01:10:38,440
Philadelphia police!
Open the door!

887
01:10:38,520 --> 01:10:41,440
I was wonderin'
when you were gonna get here.

888
01:10:49,600 --> 01:10:52,480
- Don't. Don't.
- You didn't do nothin'!
What did you do to my car?

889
01:10:52,560 --> 01:10:54,400
- That's enough. Leave him alone.
- Get outta here!

890
01:10:54,480 --> 01:10:58,320
- What did you do to my car?
- It wasn't me! It was Joey!

891
01:10:58,400 --> 01:11:00,920
- Joey, who?
- Answer his question.

892
01:11:00,960 --> 01:11:04,640
- Answer it!
- Joey Coyle! It was Joey Coyle, Dad!

893
01:11:04,720 --> 01:11:08,480
- It was Joey Coyle!
- Joey Coyle did it, huh?

894
01:11:08,560 --> 01:11:11,440
- Get in the house!
- He made me do it.
Don't hurt me, Dad, please.

895
01:11:11,520 --> 01:11:14,360
- I'm sorry, Dad! I'm sorry!
- Go be sorry in the house!

896
01:11:14,440 --> 01:11:17,080
- I'm sorry!
- Get in the house!
Yeah, you'll be sorry.

897
01:11:17,120 --> 01:11:19,200
Joey Coyle
found the money. Hey!

898
01:11:19,280 --> 01:11:22,200
Joey Coyle found the money! Yo!

899
01:11:25,160 --> 01:11:27,600
